<task id="DEVOPS-015" project="Spaarke DevOps Project Tracking r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create /devops-project-register skill (inverse handoff for backfill)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~10 minutes</actual-effort>
    <completed>2026-06-23</completed>
    <tags>skill-creation, devops, project-register, backfill, gh-cli</tags>
    <dependencies>010, 014</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Author `/devops-project-register --from-folder` skill per FR-11. Inverse direction of `/devops-project-start` — for an *existing* worktree/folder without a Project Issue, create the Project Issue and populate fields from local state. Used heavily in Phase 3 backfill.

NOTE: This task modifies `.claude/skills/` — main session only.
  </prompt>

  <role>Skill author. The inverse direction of task 014. Most logic mirrors `/devops-project-start` but the inputs come from the local folder + worktree state instead of an Issue body.</role>

  <goal>
Run against an existing `projects/{name}-r1/` folder produces a Project Issue with `Worktree Path`, `Project Folder`, `Task Count`, `Tasks Completed`, and computed `Project Status` matching local state. README pointer block written.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-07">Spaarke skill convention</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-11">Inverse direction; reuses fields from FR-02</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec D-12">Every Project has an Epic parent — `--epic` REQUIRED</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec F4">Phase 3 ordering: by Epic, then by most-recent commit activity</constraint>
    <constraint source="root CLAUDE.md §3">Main session only</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/INDEX.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/devops-project-start/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check">Confirm task 014 ✅ (reuse its patterns + helpers if extracted).</step>
    <step order="1" name="Author frontmatter + Prerequisites">Standard Spaarke skill convention.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Author Steps">(a) Read `projects/{name}/spec.md` + `README.md` + `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`. (b) Read worktree state: branch name, last commit date. (c) Compute `Task Count` = count of POML files; `Tasks Completed` = count of ✅ rows in TASK-INDEX. (d) Compute `Project Status` heuristic: open PR → In Progress; no open PR but commits in 30d → In Progress; commits older than 30d but worktree exists → On Hold; no worktree → not a candidate. (e) `gh issue create` from project template. (f) Add to Project #2. (g) Set all 6 new fields. (h) Set Parent issue Epic #E. (i) Write README pointer block (or update existing one).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Failure Modes">Folder lacks spec.md, no Epic specified, ambiguous Project Status (defer to user prompt), folder already has an Issue.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Idempotency">If Project Issue already exists for this folder, REPORT no-op + show current Issue URL.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update INDEX.md">Add row.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Smoke test">Run against a throwaway projects folder; verify Issue + fields + README pointer block.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Edit">.claude/skills/* files</tool>
    <tool name="Write">New SKILL.md</tool>
    <tool name="gh">Smoke test</tool>
    <tool name="git">Branch + commit metadata</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="skill">.claude/skills/devops-project-register/SKILL.md</output>
    <output type="config">.claude/skills/INDEX.md (one new row)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-devops-project-tracking-r1/notes/spikes/phase2-project-register-smoke-{date}.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">SKILL.md exists with NFR-07 sections</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke test produces Issue with all 6 fields populated + Parent issue Epic correct</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">README pointer block landed on local README</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Idempotency: re-run against folder-with-Issue is no-op</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">INDEX.md updated</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
